Ralf Rangnick’s choice of manager to take over from him at Manchester United has been revealed. Despite reports of the club being in secret contact with Paris Saint-Germain’s Mauricio Pochettino, the Argentine is not Rangnick’s preferred successor. Ralf Rangnick was given the privilege to make the choice of who succeeds him at the club when he leaves next summer. Pochettino, Erik ten Hag of Ajax and Leicester City’s Brendan Rodgers are top on the list of managers lining up for the job French outlet, Le Parisien reports that Rangnick prefers Ten Hag to take over the reins at Old Trafford and he is a huge fan of the 51-year-old. Ten Hag has transformed Ajax in recent seasons making them play scintillating football and they joined an exclusive club this season by winning all six of their Champions League group games. Le Parisien also reported that PSG are braced for the possibility of losing Pochettino in the summer and will move to bring in Zinedine Zidane as his replacement.